    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix invalid function pointers after LDPC library loading\n\n### Summary\nThe LDPC library loading mechanism in OAI was broken due to premature closing of shared library handles. When `load_nrLDPClib()` was called, the underlying `load_module_version_shlib()` function would load the library, extract function pointers with `dlsym()`, but then immediately call `dlclose()` on the handle. This made all the function pointers invalid, causing segfaults when the LDPC encoder/decoder functions were later invoked.\n\nThe issue was particularly evident when running PHY-level simulations or when the LDPC offload functionality was enabled, as these code paths directly use the function pointers obtained during library loading.\n\n### Changes\n- `common/utils/load_module_shlib.c`: \n  * Store library handles instead of immediately closing them\n  * Add proper cleanup functions to close handles when needed\n  * Handle library reloading by closing previous handles\n- `common/utils/load_module_shlib.h`: \n  * Add `lib_handle` field to `loader_shlibdesc_t` structure\n  * Export new cleanup functions\n\n"
}